sql:
SELECT SUM(runs_scored) AS total_runs
FROM player_statistics
WHERE player_id = 123 AND season_id = 456;

SELECT SUM(runs) AS total_runs
FROM balls
WHERE batsman_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- In cricket, a bowler's economy rate (average runs conceded) is a key metric of their performance; 
- 'Shouldered the burden of at least 11 overs' implies having bowled more than 10 overs; 
- 'Most frugal' refers to bowlers who concede the least runs on average, while 'most generous' refers to those who concede the most.

